" alt=3D"N"> is taken to infinity.
</p>
<p>
If <img src=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/images/equations/BinomialDistr=
ibution/Inline174.svg" class=3D"inlineformula" style=3D"max-height:100%;max=
-width:100%" border=3D"0" width=3D"51" height=3D"21" alt=3D"N-&gt;infty">
 and <img src=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/images/equations/BinomialDis=
tribution/Inline175.svg" class=3D"inlineformula" style=3D"max-height:100%;m=
ax-width:100%" border=3D"0" width=3D"42" height=3D"21" alt=3D"p-&gt;0">
 in such a way that <img src=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/images/equati=
ons/BinomialDistribution/Inline176.svg" class=3D"inlineformula" style=3D"ma=
x-height:100%;max-width:100%" border=3D"0" width=3D"60" height=3D"21" alt=
